------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Karpathy coding guidelines
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The `np-kb-coding-rules` skill adapts behavioral coding guidelines originally
published as "andrej-karpathy-skills" (multica-ai/andrej-karpathy-skills),
MIT License. nervepack condensed them into native coding rules, reorganized the
structure, and extended them with nervepack-specific rules.
Source: https://github.com/multica-ai/andrej-karpathy-skills

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
superpowers (process workflow patterns)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nervepack's process expectations (explore-before-build, test-first, root-cause
debugging, plan execution) are designed to compose with the "superpowers" Claude
Code plugin when it is installed. nervepack does not vendor or depend on it; it is
referenced as an optional companion process toolkit.
Source: https://github.com/obra/superpowers

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
mermaid (vendored diagram renderer)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
dashboard/vendor/mermaid.min.js is the mermaid diagramming library, MIT License,
vendored verbatim so the dashboard renders Mermaid diagrams client-side without
any external/CDN fetch (the dashboard's no-external-fetch invariant). Loaded only
on wiki pages that contain a diagram; gated by the evaluator.wiki_mermaid param.
Source: https://github.com/mermaid-js/mermaid
